title: BOLDLY ME LAUNCH TRAILER
description:
I have a PODCAST! ðŸ’›
For such a long time, we've only heard from one type of voice, one type of person, one type of experience. And, for such a long time, it led me to believe that only one voice, one person, one experience held value. 
On Boldly Me, Iâ€™ll be interviewing and showing voices of the brave, the bold, the different. People like Dylan Alcott, and Grace Tame, and Tim Minchin (I ugly sobbed the entire interview) and Lizzie VelÃ¡squezâ€¦ people who are changing our understanding of different, and ensuring a future where different is celebrated. 
To be hosting my own podcast where the voices and experiences of so many diverse humans are heard, heroed and celebrated is something I have been longing for, and something that society has needed for far too long.
I'm so excited to be stepping into this new role and for everyone to tune in.

The first episode of Boldly Me launches on Monday. Make sure to subscribe here:

title: "RISE TO IT" - THE BEST YEAR OF MY LIFE 2019
description:
The year is ending, and with it, a million-billion things that I never in my life believed would happen in my life time, never the less this year... 
And, perhaps it's a video that only I care for, perhaps it's only a video that I'm going to watch back a million times over just to say to myself in years to come 'hey, man. I really did it', but I wanted to create a montage of the year. 
Because this year I not only did some of the most exciting incredible things that make me so overjoyed and excited, but I overcame things which have been holding my down like boulders for the past decade...
This is the year that I decided that I'm taking charge.
That this life is mine, and I'm going to seize every second of it with everything I have.

I would be nowhere without the endless love and support I'm shown by the people I have the privilege of sharing my life with. I would be nowhere without this constant love and support that I'm constantly getting from you all, and I have to pinch myself daily to remind myself that this isn't a dream, that sometimes real life can be just as beautiful.
There's going to be hard parts, there's going to be downfalls... Isn't that what life is all about? Taking the ups and the downs.
But for the first time, I'm so excited about all of it. And I am so, so ready for all of it.
I love you all, endlessly. 

See you in 2020, and remember...
Your life is an occasion... 
Rise to it

title: WHAT I GOT FOR MY 21ST BIRTHDAY
description:
*Please read*
Hi, beautiful butterflies!
I debated uploading this video because I'm aware that I look tired, sound tired, act tired. I've had such a huge few weeks with massive, exciting projects and my sensory overload is at an all time high. I don't know how obvious it is, or if I'm being a typical over-thinker and... well... overthinking it?
(Ooft, isn't that an endless cycle?)
Anyway! I hope you're all having the most beautiful day! Look after yourselves, take time off, drink water, love yourself. 
This is my 21st birthday haul!

Loads of love!

xx

description:
At the end of 2015, I finished high school, and I was terrified. 
I didnâ€™t know what I wanted to do with my life. I didnâ€™t know where I wanted to beâ€¦ who I wanted to be.
God told me to trust him. God told me to give him the first year of my life, and he would bless the rest. 
I was scared. And I thought I was going crazy. 
But  jumped. I trusted him. 
At the start of 2016, I started bible college. And began the hardest year of my entire life.
At the end of 2016, I finished college, and I was eager for God to do his part. 
He promised it would happen. And so I sat and eagerly waited.
Auditions came and passed. Nothing happened.
Opportunities came and passed. Zilch.
At the start of 2017, I still saw nothing, and I began to grow frustrated. 
â€œWhatâ€™s going on, God? You promised. The year is over, and youâ€™ve given me nothing.â€ 
But just when you think youâ€™ve got things under controlâ€¦ Just when you think you donâ€™t need his stupid promisesâ€¦ he shows you that heâ€™s more powerful than anything. 
That man may fail, but God never will. 
God promised that heâ€™d bless the rest of my life, and this year has been the most blessed year I could have ever, ever imagined.
This year I won the Geelong Disability Award.
This year I starred in a movie. 
This year I travelled Australia by myself.
This year I became Australiaâ€™s first ever Extreme Cowboys Green Horse Champion.
This year I met Little Mix twice. I met Niall Horan twice. I travelled Australia to watch my favourite artists. 
This year I attended the Greatest Showman Premiere. 
This year I spoke at conferences, schools and panels all across Victoria. 
This year I spoke on national television. National radio. 
This year I made breakthroughs that should have been impossible in the natural.

This year, God showed me what he has in store for me
This year, I could be saying to myself â€˜â€˜this year has been amazing, how could it get any better?â€™

This year Iâ€™m telling myself,
 â€˜This year has been amazing. Bring on next yearâ€™

title: CHAMPIONS (We Did It)
description:
â€œFairytales can come true
But youâ€™ve got to make them happen
It all depends on youâ€.
Eight years ago, I met my fairytale in the form of a little, mangled, (slightly-murderous) crossbred pony. 
She was small, and slightly crazy. But she had the heart of a lion. 
Two years ago, I discovered Extreme Cowboys. I started with my Quarter Horse, and then decided to try it with my little scruffy ponyâ€¦. 
She took to it like a cat to waterâ€¦. (Not great.)
But we tried. And we tried, and we tried. We succeeded, and we failed, and we grew.
It wasnâ€™t easyâ€¦ But fairytales never are. 
And eventually, my determination and love for this sport weeded itâ€™s way into Marleaâ€™s own heart.
For sixteen years Iâ€™ve dreamed of having a wreath wrapped around my best friends neck, and to be handed a championship buckle. Iâ€™ve trained, and worked, and dreamed for this exact moment for as long as I can remember.
Beating a field of 13 professionals and their incredible horses, my little lion heart and I finally did it.
Extreme Cowboys Australian Championships first ever Green Horse champions.
(Next step... America)

title: This Is Me (aspergers)
description:
Hey butterflies!
My name's Chloe, and I'm an 18 year old Aspie.
After writing a blog for a while- I've now decided to start a Youtube channel, where I'll basically be talking about Aspergers and being on the spectrum. Future videos will get into more specific details about living with ASD to give insight on what it's like, as well as being a tool to possibly help other people on the spectrum.
I hope you all enjoy my first video- I can't wait for more!
